{"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" (","kind":"text"},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"text":") ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:objc(cs)NSExpression","text":"NSExpression","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" * ","kind":"text"},{"text":"hillshadeMethod","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The default value of this property is an expression that evaluates to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"standard"},{"type":"text","text":". Set this property to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" to reset it to the default value."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can set this property to an expression containing any of the following:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Constant "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MLNHillshadeMethod"},{"type":"text","text":" values"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Any of the following constant string values:"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"standard"},{"type":"text","text":": The legacy hillshade method."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"basic"},{"type":"text","text":": Basic hillshade. Uses a simple physics model where the reflected"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"light intensity is proportional to the cosine of the angle between the incident"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"light and the surface normal. Similar to GDAL’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"type":"text","text":" default algorithm."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"combined"},{"type":"text","text":": Hillshade algorithm whose intensity scales with slope. Similar"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to GDAL’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-combined"},{"type":"text","text":" option."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"igor"},{"type":"text","text":": Hillshade algorithm which tries to minimize effects on other map"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"features beneath. Similar to GDAL’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"gdaldem"},{"type":"text","text":" with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-igor"},{"type":"text","text":" option."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"multidirectional"},{"type":"text","text":": Hillshade with multiple illumination directions. Uses"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the basic hillshade model with multiple independent light sources."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Predefined functions, including mathematical and string operators"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Conditional expressions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Variable assignments and references to assigned variables"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Step functions applied to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$zoomLevel"},{"type":"text","text":" variable"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property does not support applying interpolation functions to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"$zoomLevel"},{"type":"text","text":" variable or applying interpolation or step functions to feature"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"attributes."}]}]}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"hillshadeMethod"}],"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"hillshadeMethod","kind":"identifier"}],"symbolKind":"property","roleHeading":"Instance Property","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNHillsha